modules.description: This module implements the Audioscrobbler protocol for submitting track data and managing playback status independently of HTTP clients. It defines song metadata handling, error reporting, and both basic and advanced workflows for authenticating and sending data to a scrobbling service. Concrete use cases include submitting played tracks, marking tracks as loved or skipped, and broadcasting now-playing information to a music tracking backend.

This module implements the Last.fm Radio API with functions to handle radio sessions, including parsing URIs, initializing and adjusting stations, fetching playlists, and retrieving track metadata. It works with strings for URIs and session IDs, lists of key-value pairs for track metadata, and custom error types for handling failures. Concrete use cases include authenticating a radio session, adjusting station settings, and extracting playable track URIs from a Last.fm radio feed.

Contains the API version used for interacting with the Last.fm service. Provides a single value representing the version string. Useful for ensuring compatibility with the Last.fm API in API request headers or parameters.

Implements the Last.fm Audioscrobbler and Radio APIs with functions to authenticate, submit track data, manage playback status, and handle radio sessions. Works with strings, key-value metadata, and custom error types. Used for scrobbling tracks, broadcasting now-playing info, and retrieving or adjusting radio station playlists.
